==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Qualitative
<hw>Qual"i*ta*tive</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Cf. LL.
<ets>gualitativus</ets>, F. <ets>qualitatif</ets>.]</ety> <def>Relating
to quality; having the character of quality.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Qual"i*ta*tive*ly</wf>, <pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Qualitative analysis</b></col> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>,
<cd>analysis which merely determines the constituents of a substance
without any regard to the quantity of each ingredient; -- contrasted
with <xex>quantitative analysis</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Qualitied</ent>⟦br⟧
